    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

___ TestAuthRoles.test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions ____

self = <auth_test.TestAuthRoles object at 0x7fbd2ac514e0>

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

___ TestAuthRoles.test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions ____

self = <auth_test.TestAuthRoles object at 0x7f373a70cb00>

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

___ TestAuthRoles.test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions ____

self = <auth_test.TestAuthRoles object at 0x7f3eab065438>

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

___ TestAuthRoles.test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions ____

self = <auth_test.TestAuthRoles object at 0x7f720376a898>

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

___ TestAuthRoles.test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions ____

self = <auth_test.TestAuthRoles object at 0x7fb3c17d77b8>

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

___ TestAuthRoles.test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions ____

self = <auth_test.TestAuthRoles object at 0x7fde83ae2908>

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

___ TestAuthRoles.test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions ____

self = <auth_test.TestAuthRoles object at 0x7f65ab41c400>

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

___ TestAuthRoles.test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions ____

self = <auth_test.TestAuthRoles object at 0x7fd5c0a8ff98>

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

___ TestAuthRoles.test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions ____

self = <auth_test.TestAuthRoles object at 0x7ff686462048>

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

___ TestAuthRoles.test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions ____

self = <auth_test.TestAuthRoles object at 0x7fc844c66048>

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

___ TestAuthRoles.test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions ____

self = <auth_test.TestAuthRoles object at 0x7fa64c77af28>

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

___ TestAuthRoles.test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions ____

self = <auth_test.TestAuthRoles object at 0x7fb41b1bd710>

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")

___ TestAuthRoles.test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions ____

self = <auth_test.TestAuthRoles object at 0x7fdd7c1aa588>

    def test_drop_function_and_keyspace_cleans_up_udf_permissions(self):
        """
            * Launch a one node cluster
            * Connect as the default superuser
            * Create a new role, 'mike'
            * Create a UDF
            * Grant mike permissions on the UDF, and on the keyspace of the UDF
            * Verify dropping the UDF removes mike's permissions for the UDF
            * Verify dropping the keyspace removes the rest of mike's permissions
            """
        self.setup_table()
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE ROLE mike WITH PASSWORD = '12345' AND LOGIN = true")
        self.superuser.execute("CREATE FUNCTION ks.plus_one ( input int ) CALLED ON NULL INPUT RETURNS int LANGUAGE javascript AS 'input + 1'")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ks.plus_one(int) TO mike")
        self.superuser.execute("GRANT EXECUTE ON ALL FUNCTIONS IN KEYSPACE ks TO mike")
    
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE"),
                                        ("mike", "<function ks.plus_one(int)>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
    
        # drop the function
        self.superuser.execute("DROP FUNCTION ks.plus_one")
        self.assert_permissions_listed([("mike", "<all functions in ks>", "EXECUTE")],
                                       self.superuser,
                                       "LIST ALL PERMISSIONS OF mike")
        # drop the keyspace
>       self.superuser.execute("DROP KEYSPACE ks")
